ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I thought the course was well taught and intellectually stimulating. I would recommend it for those reasons.

I would definitely recommend this course to other first year grad students. It has helped me to understand primary literature on these subjects, as well as the research discussed during many presentations.
I would recommend this class to a friend.
I would recommend it, though it is very easy and feels like an undergrad course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I thought the course was well taught and intellectually stimulating. It did not contribute to my research.
This course did not really contribute to my research.
I enjoyed having a human disease context for all of the physiological information we were learning.
